title: Magnitude 4.1 aftershock jolts Surigao City
text:
Nation   Magnitude 4.1 aftershock jolts Surigao City By Rosette Adel (philstar.com)   12:52pm The magnitude 4.1 earthquake occurred at 11:01 a.m. Phivolcs 
MANILA, Philippines — A magnitude 4.1 tremor shook Surigao City, Surigao del Norte anew on Sunday morning. 
The Philippine Institute of Volcanology and Seismology (Phivolcs) said the tremor felt at Intensity III in Surigao City is an aftershock of the magnitude 6.7 earthquake that hit the city last Friday night. 
The magnitude 4.1 earthquake occurred at 11:01 a.m. Its epicenter was traced 9 kilometers North 87° west of Surigao City, Surigao del Norte. 
It has 15 kilometers depth of focus and was determined to be tectonic in origin. 
The aftershock reportedly caused panic among residents staying at the Surigao City Gym who are waiting for President Rodrigo Duterte. The president is set to visit the area to personally check on the damage and the people affected. 
Aside from magnitude 4.1 quake, almost 20 other tremors were recorded on Saturday mostly in Surigao City and San Jose, Dinagat Islands. Nation   
In its advisory, Phivolcs said it is not expecting damage nor aftershock from the recent quake. Nation
